                  <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1" type="birth">ዮሐንስ፡ አፈ፡ ወርቅ፡</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">Yoḥannǝs ʾAfa Warq</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="en" corresp="#n1" type="main">John Chrysostom</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="en" xml:id="n2" type="nick">Chrysostomos 'Golden mouthed' </persName>
                  <occupation type="ecclesiastic">writer </occupation>
                  
                
                  <nationality type="Greece"/>
                  <faith type="Greek"/>
                  
                  <birth> 347, he was born in Antioch  in <date> 347/350</date>
               </birth>
                  <residence/>
                  <floruit>He was the bishop of Constantinople and is regarded as the greatest preacher of the Greek Church. He lived a hermit life in the years <date> 371-377</date>. 
                     He was ordained  as a priest in <date> 386</date> and then he preached in the Church of Antioch for 12 years. Then, in  <date> 397</date> he became the patriarch of Constantinople.
                     He was an extraordinary writer whose works were also translated into Gǝʿǝz. 
                    
                  </floruit>
                  <death>407</death>
               </person>
               
         </listPerson>
         
